SIMPLE: poplar
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Poplar
<hw>Pop"lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>popler</ets>, OF. <ets>poplier</ets>, F. <ets>peuplier</ets>, fr.
L. <ets>populus</ets> poplar.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Any tree of the genus <gen>Populus</gen>; also, the timber, which
is soft, and capable of many uses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The aspen poplar is <spn>Populus tremula</spn> and
<spn>Populus tremuloides</spn>; Balsam poplar is <spn>Populus
balsamifera</spn>; Lombardy poplar (<spn>Populus dilatata</spn>) is a
tall, spiry tree; white poplar is <spn>Populus alba</spn>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The timber of the tulip tree; -- called also
<altname>white poplar</altname>.</def> <mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Poplexy</ent>⟦br⟧
